The paper deals with graph drawing and optimization of graph readability, which are topics commonly studied in computer science subfields such as computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), social and information networks (cs.SI), and graph theory (cs.GR). The paper's focus on measuring and maximizing resolution further supports these potential sub-categories.
